1776383425356233	edict-dev	itc:v3:AWLkkmTOfzk5kQAAAAAAQeqtbv7rtAAAAAEvzgE		item.create	bn-3k5f	{"description":"When all unblocked bones are L/XL without subtasks, 'bn next --json' emits a warn line then a {\"message\": \"...decomposition...\"} JSON object on stdout. parse_ready_count fails to parse (warn prefix breaks JSON) or sees no assignments, so has_work() returns false and dev-loop idles. But dev-loop is the thing that SHOULD decompose these. Fix has_work() to recognize the decompose-first signal and return true. Also make parse_ready_count robust to warn prefixes. Add tests covering both cases.","kind":"task","size":"s","title":"dev-loop: handle bn next decompose-first as has_work"}	blake3:ZWBaB4oWD5AbLWQxLmuIyvxn5yYxneDAS-EfCNT4CVY
